{"questionId":"9854","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following table shows the costs in US dollars (US$) of direct flights between six cities.&nbsp;Blank cells indicate no direct flights. The rows represent the departure cities. The columns&nbsp;represent the destination cities.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/05aa504e313ed549aca811cb8f4c520ff5322987.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following table shows the least cost to travel between the cities.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/b147f2eefdf086bcf0b4f7c33c0250d2bbf51152.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the values of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\"> <mi>a</mi> </math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"> <mi>b</mi> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a = 230\"> <mi>a</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>230</mn> </math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b = 340\"> <mi>b</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>340</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9854","referenceCode":"SPM.2.AHL.TZ0.5e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the values of a and b .","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.16—Tree and cycle algorithms, Chinese postman, travelling salesman"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}